Define \(D = X - Y\). Since \(X\) and \(Y\) are independent, \(D\) follows a normal distribution. The mean of \(D\) is \(\mu_D = \mu_X - \mu_Y = 800 - 850 = -50\). The variance of \(D\) is \(\sigma_D^2 = \sigma_X^2 + \sigma_Y^2 = 14400 + 2500 = 16900\), so the standard deviation is \(\sigma_D = \sqrt{16900} = 130\). Thus, \(D \sim N(-50, 16900)\).

The probability required is \(P(D > 15)\). Standardize to a standard normal variable:  
\[
