- Sum of \(P(A_i \cap A_j)\) for \(i \neq j\): \(\frac{1}{9} + \frac{1}{9} + \frac{1}{9} = \frac{3}{9} = \frac{1}{3}\)
- Thus, \(1 - \frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{27}\)

Now compute:
- \(1 - \frac{1}{3} = \frac{2}{3}\)
- \(\frac{2}{3} + \frac{1}{27} = \frac{18}{27} + \frac{1}{27} = \frac{19}{27}\)

