Solution: The sample size required to estimate the mean strength with a maximum error of 0.25 at a 98% confidence level is determined using the formula for sample size in estimating a population mean when the population standard deviation is unknown. The sample standard deviation \(s = 1.723\) from the preliminary sample is used as an estimate for the population standard deviation.

